00:39:18,590 --> 00:39:19,951
Yeah. Listen...

754
00:39:19,975 --> 00:39:21,803
You didn't ask for a sister,

755
00:39:21,827 --> 00:39:23,971
and you probably don't need one.

756
00:39:23,995 --> 00:39:26,424
Your parents send
you singing fish.

757
00:39:26,448 --> 00:39:30,099
You're very accomplished for
your age, and you seem very happy.

758
00:39:30,168 --> 00:39:32,246
So, you can go if you want.

759
00:39:32,270 --> 00:39:34,604
I can understand
why you would want to.

760
00:39:34,673 --> 00:39:38,193
But I would like to show you
something if you have a minute.

761
00:39:39,895 --> 00:39:43,312
<i>They say we can
repress our memories.</i>

762
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:46,415
<i>I wonder if we're just
keeping them safe somewhere.</i>

763
00:39:49,054 --> 00:39:52,688
She wrote in these
journals, obsessively.

764
00:39:53,992 --> 00:39:56,525
Mostly surgical notes, ideas,

765
00:39:56,594 --> 00:40:00,746
but this one is from around
the time you were born.

766
00:40:05,119 --> 00:40:07,854
"A surgery can fail for
any number of reasons,

767
00:40:07,923 --> 00:40:10,840
"whether from a
patient's morbidity

768
00:40:10,909 --> 00:40:13,009
"or surgeon's ineptitude." Jeez.

769
00:40:14,045 --> 00:40:15,744
They're not so warm.

770
00:40:16,430 --> 00:40:18,197
She wasn't, either.

771
00:40:18,266 --> 00:40:20,466
But there is more to her than...

772
00:40:22,220 --> 00:40:26,122
I'm still finding out
things about her myself.

773
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:28,791
<i>Because no matter
how painful they are,</i>

774
00:40:28,859 --> 00:40:31,844
<i>they are our most
valuable possessions.</i>

775
00:40:36,301 --> 00:40:41,087
<i>Our lives are built on our
mistakes as much as our successes.</i>

776
00:40:41,156 --> 00:40:42,784
She wrote mostly at night,

777
00:40:42,808 --> 00:40:47,109
with a glass of wine, as you
can see by the ring stains and...

778
00:40:47,178 --> 00:40:51,864
But I think here is
when she found out

779
00:40:51,933 --> 00:40:55,268
she was pregnant
because the wine stains stop

780
00:40:55,337 --> 00:40:58,271
and she starts writing
down everything she ate.

781
00:40:59,741 --> 00:41:01,807
So... This was when she...

782
00:41:01,876 --> 00:41:04,196
Realized she was
pregnant with you.

783
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:08,160
So she wanted you to be okay.

784
00:41:08,983 --> 00:41:10,700
She wanted to be healthy.

785
00:41:12,571 --> 00:41:14,704
She tried, at least.

786
00:41:18,460 --> 00:41:20,810
<i>They made us who we are.</i>

787
00:41:28,620 --> 00:41:30,886
<i>The first time I won
the Harper Avery,</i>

788
00:41:30,955 --> 00:41:34,657
<i>I dedicated it to the men
who'd been so supportive.</i>

789
00:41:36,427 --> 00:41:39,695
<i>No, I wish. Just kidding.</i>

790
00:41:39,764 --> 00:41:41,997
<i>The first time I won
the Harper Avery,</i>

791
00:41:42,066 --> 00:41:45,134
<i>I thought, "Screw
all those boys."</i>

792
00:41:46,437 --> 00:41:48,904
<i>I stood there,
holding that trophy,</i>

793
00:41:48,973 --> 00:41:53,176
<i>and I thought about
everything I'd sacrificed,</i>

794
00:41:53,244 --> 00:41:55,178
<i>what I had overcome.</i>

795
00:41:56,814 --> 00:41:59,982
<i>And I dedicated that award</i>

796
00:42:00,051 --> 00:42:03,919
<i>to all the women surgeons
who would come after me.</i>

797
00:42:15,066 --> 00:42:16,465
<i>Where were we?</i>
